    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-08-07T22:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-08-07T22:00:00-05:00" n="501"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d501">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.24/1399: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-08-08T10:00:00+07:00"
                            >August 8, 1942—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received August 8—7:33 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>920. Embassy’s 836, July 13, noon. Embassy understands from Kwok, Director of
                    Foreign Trade Office of NRC,<note n="18" xml:id="d501fn18">National Resources
                        Commission, Chinese Ministry of Economic Affairs.</note> that agreement has
                    been reached with Russians by Wong Wen-hao (who has not yet returned from
                    northwest) to exchange during this year 2,000 tons strategic materials desired
                    by Russian for equal weight of supplies for China (primarily gasoline) the point
                    of exchange to be Hami, transportation to be by truck.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gauss</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
